# Git LFS — automatically track large generated figure artifacts.
#
# This is a PROSPECTIVE rule: it only affects PNGs added at or after the
# commit that introduces this file. Existing PNG blobs in the repo's history
# remain as regular git objects until a separate `git lfs migrate import`
# rewrite is run (see PR #11 discussion — that step is destructive and
# coordinated separately).
# Why scoped to `research/observations/figures/`: PNGs elsewhere (e.g. UI
# screenshots in testing/gui/frontend/, small icons, theme assets) are
# typically small and don't benefit from LFS. Research figures are the
# class of file that has measurably bloated the repo (~16.8 MB across 36
# files in PR #11).
research/observations/figures/*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
